KIRO, update the byDebut hackathon MVP frontend and onboarding UX so the platform can place each user into the most appropriate creative role instead of only asking them to manually choose one. The frontend must feel like an intelligent role-discovery and collaboration interface, not just a simple form app.

The frontend must be redesigned around a guided onboarding flow with role recommendation, role confirmation, and role-specific workspace views.

Use:
- HTML
- Vanilla JavaScript
- CSS
- no frontend framework unless absolutely necessary

The frontend must include the following screens and behaviors:

1. Landing Page
Create a polished landing page for byDebut with:
- product name
- one-sentence value proposition
- short explanation that byDebut connects writers, actors, reviewers, and AI to build YouTube-ready creative projects
- a primary CTA button: "Start Your Creative Role Discovery"
- a secondary CTA button: "View Demo Flow"
- a visual section that explains the 6 engines:
  Identity Engine
  Matching Engine
  Project Assembly Engine
  Creative Production Engine
  Review and Quality Engine
  Distribution and Growth Engine

2. Role Discovery Screen
Instead of immediately asking users to select a role, first present a guided discovery questionnaire.

This screen must ask:
- What do you most want to contribute?
  options:
  writing ideas
  performing characters
  evaluating and improving stories
  validating specialized knowledge
- What excites you most?
  options:
  creating narratives
  embodying emotions
  analyzing quality
  checking technical accuracy
- What kind of output do you want to influence?
  options:
  script
  performance
  quality
  expertise
- How do you prefer to help a project succeed?
  options:
  invent the story
  represent the character
  improve the narrative
  validate correctness
- Which description fits you best?
  options:
  I express ideas through writing
  I want to perform and be seen in stories
  I like reviewing and giving feedback
  I contribute specialized professional insight

After answering, calculate a frontend role recommendation score for:
- writer
- actor
- reviewer
- specialist

Use a simple scoring model in the frontend and send the answers to the backend as well.

Display a result screen:
- "Recommended Role: Writer / Actor / Reviewer / Specialist"
- show confidence score
- show 2-3 bullets explaining why this role fits
- provide a button:
  "Continue with this role"
- also provide:
  "Choose a different role manually"

For the hackathon MVP, if specialist is recommended, allow the user to continue as reviewer-specialist or reviewer with specialization so the system remains within the MVP scope.

3. Role Confirmation Screen
After role recommendation, show a role confirmation step.

This screen must:
- summarize the recommended role
- explain what this role does inside byDebut
- show what the user will be able to do next
- allow user to confirm or switch role

Role descriptions:

Writer:
creates ideas, scripts, fragments, scenes, essays, and narrative concepts

Actor:
represents characters, emotional tone, performance style, and audience-facing interpretation

Reviewer:
evaluates narrative clarity, emotional impact, coherence, and audience engagement

Specialist:
validates content from a professional or technical perspective; for MVP, map this into reviewer with specialization

